---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Hobbies">
  <div class="index-content framed">
    <h1>Hobbies</h1>
    <p>
      Outside of software, I spend most of my creative time around tabletop
      RPGs: running games, designing adventures, and building community spaces
      where people can reliably find a table. I also like experimenting with
      automation and AI-assisted workflows for practical projects.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="hobby-section">
    <h2>Dungeons & Dragons</h2>
    <div class="hobby-content">
      <p>
        I enjoy the full loop of the hobby: worldbuilding, encounter design, and
        collaborative storytelling. I tend to run games with a "player-first"
        mindset and focus on making it easy for new players to get started.
      </p>

      <div class="hobby-details">
        <h3>What I like most</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Worldbuilding and long-running story arcs</li>
          <li>Session facilitation and improvisation</li>
          <li>Designing one-shots and reusable modules</li>
          <li>Helping new players onboard quickly</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>How it overlaps with my engineering</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Building tools and workflows that reduce scheduling friction</li>
          <li>
            Creating lightweight systems for event signups and coordination
          </li>
          <li>Automation for repetitive community ops tasks</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="hobby-section">
    <h2>Smokebomb Studios</h2>
    <div class="hobby-content">
      <p>
        Smokebomb Studios is my community-building outlet: a platform centered
        on tabletop RPGs in India, spanning online play, learning resources, and
        IRL events. The goal is simple: make it easier for people to discover
        TTRPGs, find consistent games, and meet the local community.
      </p>

      <div class="hobby-details">
        <h3>Current focus</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Living Chronicles:</strong> a plug-and-play campaign format where
            multiple DMs contribute to a shared world, so players can drop in when
            they are free.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>IRL events:</strong> conventions and city events that bring players
            together around a shared storyline.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Explore</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://www.smokebombstudios.com/projects/living-chronicles"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noreferrer"
            >
              Living Chronicles
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://www.smokebombstudios.com/projects/irl-events"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noreferrer"
            >
              IRL Events
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://www.smokebombstudios.com/bangalore-dd-con"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noreferrer"
            >
              Bangalore D&D Con
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://www.smokebombstudios.com/delhi-dd-tour"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noreferrer"
            >
              Delhi D&D Tour
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hobby-section {
    margin: 3rem 0;
    border: 2px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--card-bg);
  }

  .hobby-section h2 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }

  .hobby-content p {
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .hobby-details h3 {
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .hobby-details ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .hobby-details li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 684px) {
    .hobby-section {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
